⸻

What is currently happening in the business

Let’s understand how data usually exists in an e-commerce company.

1. Orders data is in one system

The order management system stores:

* what product was purchased
* how much was paid
* when the order happened
* what payment method was used
* which country the order came from

This tells us what was bought.

But it does not tell us what happened before the purchase.

⸻

2. Clickstream data is in another system

The website/app tracking system stores:

* what product was viewed
* what was searched
* which product was added to cart
* whether checkout started
* what traffic source the user came from
* which device they used

This tells us customer behavior.

But it does not always tell us whether behavior turned into revenue.

⸻

3. Product data is in another file/system

The merchandising or catalog team stores:

* product category
* brand
* selling price
* inventory status

This tells us product context.

But it does not tell us how customers interacted with it.

⸻

4. Global business data needs enrichment

If the company sells in multiple countries:

* orders may come in USD, INR, EUR, GBP
* shipping experience differs by region
* holidays affect purchasing patterns

Without enrichment:

* revenue comparison is wrong
* global reporting is inconsistent
* business cannot fairly compare countries

⸻

So what is the actual gap?

The company has pieces of the story, but not the full story.

They can see:

* orders
* clicks
* products
* regions
* currency data

But these are disconnected.

As a result, business teams cannot easily answer end-to-end questions like:

“Customers from which traffic source viewed products, added them to cart, but did not buy?”

or

“Which category gets huge traffic but poor conversion?”

or

“Which countries look weak only because the revenue is in different currencies and not standardized?”

or

“Which customers browse repeatedly and are likely high-value customers?”

So the project goal is to connect all these pieces into one analytics pipeline.

